sequenceDiagram
    participant Sender as External SMTP Sender
    participant MX as MX Server
    participant Spam as Spam Filter
    participant Meta as Mailbox Metadata Store
    participant Blob as Content-Addressed Object Store
    participant Index as Per-User Search Index

    Note over Sender,MX: Inbound delivery
    Sender->>MX: SMTP DATA (message + attachments)
    MX->>MX: TLS, basic protocol checks

    Note over MX,Spam: Authentication + classification
    MX->>Spam: Verify SPF / DKIM / DMARC
    alt Auth fails / forged
        Spam-->>MX: Reject (5xx)
        MX-->>Sender: Bounce
    else Auth passes
        Spam->>Spam: ML classifier (headers, body, links)
        alt Classified spam
            Spam->>Meta: Deliver to Spam folder (user shard)
        else Clean
            Spam->>Meta: Deliver to Inbox (user shard)
        end
    end

    Note over Meta,Blob: Storage with dedup
    Meta->>Blob: PUT body by SHA256(content)
    alt Hash already exists
        Blob-->>Meta: Existing key (dedup ref-count++)
    else New blob
        Blob-->>Meta: Stored
    end
    Meta->>Meta: Append (user_id, msg_id) -> headers + body_hash + attachment_hashes

    Note over Meta,Index: Search index update
    Meta-)Index: Tokenize subject + body, update inverted index for user
    Meta-)Sender: Push notification to user device
